# quotetool — conda and PySide6

## Before any `python` command

The prompt **must** show `(quotetool)`, not `(base)`.

```powershell
conda activate quotetool
cd C:\Projects\quotetool
python -m src.main
```

`ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'PySide6'` almost always means the **wrong conda env** (usually `base`). PySide6 is installed only in `quotetool`.

## Verify

```powershell
conda activate quotetool
python -c "from PySide6.QtWidgets import QApplication; print('OK')"
```

## Install / repair (pip only in `quotetool` env)

```powershell
conda deactivate
conda env remove -n quotetool -y
conda create -n quotetool python=3.12 pip -c conda-forge -y
conda activate quotetool
pip install cadquery PySide6 pyvista pyvistaqt
```

Do **not** run `conda install pyside6` or `conda install vtk` in the same env after pip — causes DLL errors on Windows.

## DLL load failed (QtWidgets / QtCore)

Same as above: recreate env with pip-only GUI stack. Do not mix conda Qt with pip PySide6.
